### **One Axiom, Two States, Two Operations:**  
- **Continuum Hypothesis (CH):**  
  Different proof methods yield different conclusions (GÃ¶del & Cohen proved CH is independent of ZFC).  
  - In **open systems**, CH may hold under equivalence.  
  - In **closed systems**, CH may failâ€”forcing comparison requires a higher superset (e.g., large cardinal axioms).  
  - No fixed rules are needed; **category-theoretic communication suffices.**  

